  {Value: "CalStateApply", Label: "Cal State Apply"}
  {Value: "UWSystem", Label: "Universities of Wisconsin"}
  {Value: "ApplyIdaho", Label: "Apply Idaho"}
  {Value: "GAFutures", Label: "GAfutures"}
  {Value: "CFNC", Label: "NC College Connect"}
  {Value: "FloridaSUS", Label: "Florida SUS"}

Update api/internal/search/datasource.go (~L113-120):
- Rename SourceCommonApp -> SourceApplicationPlatforms
- Update ID to "application-platforms", name/description to be platform-agnostic
- Update all references in registry.go

Run `make web-schema-sync` to regenerate web/schema.graphql.

No DB migration needed — enum values live in Go code and JSONB data.

## Quality Gate
After all changes:
1. Run `make api-generate` first (in case gqlgen needs regen)
2. Run `make web-schema-sync`
3. Run `make test-standard` (covers both Go and web)

## Git
- Branch: worktree/enum-update
- Commit with a descriptive message when done
- Do NOT merge to main
